r1631 | Burlex | 2007-09-24 10:04:27 +1000 (Mon, 24 Sep 2007) | 2 lines

* removed World::MSTIME (saving a gettimeofday syscall every loop), this would be 50ms out anyway so theres no point keeping it around. (i still <3 my UNIXTIME though.)
* removed World::UNIXTIME (use the UNIXTIME static variable provided by log framework instead)
------------------------------------------------------------------------
r1630 | Burlex | 2007-09-24 09:58:56 +1000 (Mon, 24 Sep 2007) | 1 line

* network code will now use AcceptEx (event will get triggered on socket accept message) instead of wasting a accept() syscall every loop. still need to finish *nix code for this.
