r1094 | Burlex | 2007-08-16 12:06:45 +1000 (Thu, 16 Aug 2007) | 1 line

* Players will no longer freeze up on loading in a populated area. :D
------------------------------------------------------------------------
r1093 | Burlex | 2007-08-16 10:01:41 +1000 (Thu, 16 Aug 2007) | 2 lines

* Packet buffer overflow handlers. Now packets will be allocated in memory in a seperate queue and then unloaded as the client catches up. This is useful if you have a *lot* of objects or players in one area at once, and when people join it causes disconnects/freezesups/buffer overflows.
* Socket send/recv buffer sizes are now customizable via the config file. Do *not* play with this if you don't know what you're doing.
------------------------------------------------------------------------
r1092 | Burlex | 2007-08-16 08:30:49 +1000 (Thu, 16 Aug 2007) | 2 lines

* compile error fix
* larger a9 packets will now be compressed stronger.
